he expects the total to exceed 100000 next year although us law 
will allow no more than 94000 to get formal refugee status which 
entitles them to a wide range of services including english lessons 
such services cost taxpayers about 2000 for each refugee in the 
first year after arrival and often additional thousands in following 
years a precise figure cannot be calculated robinson said in an 
interview tuesday 
